cs.DS, cs.IR, cs.DC, cs.AL, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper proposes an algorithm for computing the sparse suffix array and the sparse longest common prefix array of a text, which are fundamental data structures in string processing.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the sparse suffix array and the sparse longest common prefix array are used in text indexing and search.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possibility as the paper mentions the online nature of the algorithm, which could be useful in distributed or parallel computing environments.
- cs.AL (Automata and Formal Languages) is a possibility as the paper deals with string processing, which is closely related to automata and formal languages.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possibility as the paper provides a time complexity analysis of the proposed algorithm.
